694&s=NGDPD%2CPPPGDP%2CNGDPDPC%2CPPPPC&grp=0&a= |title=World Economic Outlook Database, October 2019 |publisher=[[International Monetary Fund]] |website=IMF.org |access-date=26 December 2019}}</ref>\n*{{Increase}} $1.217 trillion ([[Purchasing power parity|PPP]], 2019 est.)<ref name=\"IMFWEONG\"/>}}\n|gdp rank        = {{plainlist|\n*[[List of countries by GDP (nominal)|27th (nominal, 2019)]]\n*[[List of countries by GDP (PPP)|23rd (PPP, 2019)]]}}\n|growth          = {{plainlist|\n*0.8%&nbsp;(2017) 1.9%&nbsp;(2018)\n*2.0%&nbsp;(2019e) 2.1%&nbsp;(2020f)<ref name=\"World Bank\">{{cite web |url=https://openknowledge.worldbank.org/bitstream/handle/10986/33044/9781464814693.pdf |title=Global Economic Prospects, January 2020 : Slow Growth, Policy Challenges |page=147 |publisher=[[World Bank]] |website=openknowledge.worldbank.org |access-date=17 January 2020}}</ref>}}\n|per capita      = {{plainlist|\n*{{Increase}} $2,222 (nominal, 2019 est.)<ref name=\"IMFWEONG\"/>\n*{{Increase}} $6,055 ([[Purchasing power parity|PPP]], 2019 est.)<ref name=\"IMFWEONG\"/>}}\n|per capita rank = {{plainlist|\n*[[List of countries by GDP (nominal) per capita|138th (nominal, 2019)]]\n*[[List of countries by GDP (PPP) per capita|131st (PPP, 2019)]]}}\n|sectors         = {{plainlist|\n*[[Primary sector of the economy|agriculture]]: 21.6%\n*[[Secondary sector of the economy|industry]]: 18.3%\n*[[Tertiary sector of the economy|services]]: 60.1% \n*(2017 est.)<ref name=\"CIA World Fact Book - Nigeria\">{{cite web |url=https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/resources/the-world-factbook/geos/ni.html|title=The World Factbook |publisher=[[Central Intelligence Agency]] |website=CIA.gov |access-date=8 February 2019}}</ref>}}\n|components      =\n|inflation       = {{DecreasePositive}} 11.4% (2018)<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.vanguardngr.com/2019/02/breaking-nigerias-inflation-rate-drops-to-11-37-per-cent-nbs/|title=Breaking: Nigeria\u2019s inflation rate drops to 11.37 per cent \u2013 NBS}}</ref>\n